kindred.network.messages

Enum ServerToClientMessage

  • Object
    • Enum<ServerToClientMessage>
      • kindred.network.messages.ServerToClientMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ServerToClientMessage>

    public enum ServerToClientMessage
extends Enum<ServerToClientMessage>
    Contains an enum number for every type of message the Server can send to the Client. Can also encode and decode these values to shorten and simplify Server to Client messages.
    Author:
    Kindred Team

      • SUCC_JOIN

        public static final ServerToClientMessage SUCC_JOIN
        Confirmation that the user has successfully joined the room. The argument is a pipe-separated string containing:
        • opponent's name
        • order of turns (1 if the player starts, or 2 otherwise)
        • map name

      • INFO_SOMEONE_ENTERED_ROOM

        public static final ServerToClientMessage INFO_SOMEONE_ENTERED_ROOM
        Confirmation that someone has successfully entered the room that the user hosts. The argument is a pipe-separated string containing:

        • Order of turns (1 if the player starts, or 2 otherwise).
        • Map name.
